<%- include('partials/header') %>
<link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/fan-to-fame.css">
<nav class="nav-bar">
        <a href="#" class="nav-logo">FAN TO FAME</a>
        <div class="nav-links">
            <a href="#story">Story</a>
            <a href="#characters">Characters</a>
            <a href="#chapters">Chapters</a>
            <a href="#quotes">Quotes</a>
            <a href="#journey">Journey</a>
        </div>
    </nav>

    <!-- HERO SECTION -->
    <header class="hero-container">
        <h1 class="hero-title">FAN TO FAME</h1>
        <p class="hero-author">Written by Deva Harsha V</p>
        
        <!-- INTEGRATED POSTER DISPLAY -->
        <div class="cover-wrapper">
            <img class="cover-image" src="https://cdn-gcs.inkitt.com/vertical_storycovers/cb10c30a92f839740cfb82d28d599b93.jpg" alt="Fan to Fame Official Book Poster">
        </div>

        <p class="hero-tagline">“Sometimes, to understand life, you have to live someone else's.”</p>
        <p class="hero-hook">A fading Bollywood superstar drowning in bitterness and a fiercely loyal fan from Rajahmundry wake up trapped in each other's bodies[cite: 1]. Can they rewrite each other's broken destinies?</p>
        
        <a href="#story" class="scroll-indicator">
            <span>Explore The Experience</span>
            <div class="scroll-arrow"></div>
        </a>
    </header>

    <!-- STORY SECTION -->
    <section id="story">
        <span class="section-label">The Concept</span>
        <h2 class="section-title">Two Lives, <span>One Fractured Mirror</span></h2>
        
        <div class="story-grid">
            <div>
                <blockquote class="story-main-quote">
                    "A pulse of radiant energy surged from the center of their chests, as if some invisible thread had been tugged violently."
                </blockquote>
                <div class="story-body">
                    <p>In the small town of Rajahmundry, 24-year-old <strong>Ravi Kumar</strong> is known as a fool[cite: 1]. He spends his family's scarce money printing banners and celebrating the birthday of his lifelong idol, <strong>Aryan Kapoor</strong>[cite: 1], a faded superstar whose career is in a catastrophic freefall amid scandals and alcoholism in a lonely Mumbai mansion[cite: 1].</p>
                    <p>On the midnight of March 5th, under an ominous, cloudless sky, both men make a desperate wish to escape their own realities[cite: 1]. Instantly, cosmic intervention shatters time, forcing their souls to swap bodies. What follows is not a game of superficial glamour, but a profound psychological dive into identity, empathy, and cosmic redemption.</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="themes-container">
                    <h3 class="themes-title">Core Themes</h3>
                    <div class="theme-tags">
                        <span class="theme-tag">Identity Cosmic Swap</span>
                        <span class="theme-tag">Empathy & Catharsis</span>
                        <span class="theme-tag">The Burden of Fame</span>
                        <span class="theme-tag">Unconditional Faith</span>
                        <span class="theme-tag">Redemption</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <aside class="stats-sidebar">
                <div class="stat-card">
                    <span class="stat-val">11</span>
                    <span class="stat-lbl">Chapters Content Grid</span>
                </div>
                <div class="stat-card">
                    <span class="stat-val">2</span>
                    <span class="stat-lbl">Parallel Narrators</span>
                </div>
                <div class="stat-card">
                    <span class="stat-val">Dual City</span>
                    <span class="stat-lbl">Mumbai & Rajahmundry</span>
                </div>
                <div class="stat-card">
                    <span class="stat-val">Drama</span>
                    <span class="stat-lbl">Story Genre</span>
                </div>
            </aside>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- CHARACTERS SECTION -->
    <section id="characters" style="background-color: #090c12;">
        <span class="section-label">The Players</span>
        <h2 class="section-title">Souls <span>Behind the Facade</span></h2>
        
        <div class="character-grid">
            <!-- Ravi -->
            <div class="char-card main-char">
                <div class="char-header">
                    <h3 class="char-name">Ravi Kumar</h3>
                    <span class="char-role">The Devoted Fan</span>
                </div>
                <p class="char-desc">A 24-year-old from Rajahmundry who faces intense poverty and constant mockery from his family and neighbors[cite: 1]. He finds his inner strength and confidence exclusively by channeling the early characters of his cinematic idol, Aryan Kapoor[cite: 1].</p>
                <div class="traits-container">
                    <span class="trait-tag">Unshakable Faith</span>
                    <span class="trait-tag">Humble</span>
                    <span class="trait-tag">Radically Honest</span>
                    <span class="trait-tag">Empathetic</span>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Aryan -->
            <div class="char-card main-char">
                <div class="char-header">
                    <h3 class="char-name">Aryan Kapoor</h3>
                    <span class="char-role">The Fallen Icon</span>
                </div>
                <p class="char-desc">Once the undisputed crown jewel of Indian cinema, now isolated inside a colossal Bandra villa[cite: 1]. He is consumed by bitterness, an identity crisis, irrelevance, and heavy drinking as the modern industry leaves his arrogance behind.</p>
                <div class="traits-container">
                    <span class="trait-tag">Cynical</span>
                    <span class="trait-tag">Defensive Ego</span>
                    <span class="trait-tag">Deeply Broken</span>
                    <span class="trait-tag">Vocal Talent</span>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Supporting: Amma -->
            <div class="char-card">
                <div class="char-header">
                    <h3 class="char-name">Ravi's Mother</h3>
                    <span class="char-role">Supporting Character</span>
                </div>
                <p class="char-desc">An exhausted, practical woman weathering severe financial hardship[cite: 1]. Her bitterness toward Ravi's obsession stems from maternal terror that her son is completely destroying his real life for an illusion[cite: 1].</p>
                <div class="traits-container">
                    <span class="trait-tag">Weathered</span>
                    <span class="trait-tag">Skeptical</span>
                    <span class="trait-tag">Protective</span>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Supporting: Vikas Rawat -->
            <div class="char-card">
                <div class="char-header">
                    <h3 class="char-name">Vikas Rawat</h3>
                    <span class="char-role">The Antagonist</span>
                </div>
                <p class="char-desc">Aryan's corrupt former manager who was fired years prior for massive financial embezzlement. He harbored a deep grudge and targeted the newly transformed star through blackmail, media leaks, and violence.</p>
                <div class="traits-container">
                    <span class="trait-tag">Vengeful</span>
                    <span class="trait-tag">Shallow Morals</span>
                    <span class="trait-tag">Manipulative</span>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- CHAPTERS SECTION -->
    <section id="chapters">
        <span class="section-label">The Manuscript</span>
        <h2 class="section-title">Chapters <span>Chronicle</span></h2>
        
        <div class="chapters-grid">
            <div class="chapter-card">
                <div>
                    <span class="chap-num">Chapter 1</span>
                    <h3 class="chap-title">The Last Believer</h3>
                </div>
                <p class="chap-teaser">Ravi celebrates his idol's birthday in an empty hall while facing a devastating domestic storm over his absolute loyalty to a fallen star[cite: 1].</p>
            </div>

            <div class="chapter-card">
                <div>
                    <span class="chap-num">Chapter 2</span>
                    <h3 class="chap-title">The Cracked Mirror</h3>
                </div>
                <p class="chap-teaser">In a luxury Bandra apartment, Aryan Kapoor wallows in alcohol and isolation. At midnight, a terrifying metaphysical bond strikes two distant cities.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="chapter-card">
                <div>
                    <span class="chap-num">Chapter 3</span>
                    <h3 class="chap-title">Stranger in My Skin</h3>
                </div>
                <p class="chap-teaser">Morning brings utter panic as both men wake up looking into mirrors showing faces they don't own. They meet briefly in a dreamlike void.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="chapter-card">
                <div>
                    <span class="chap-num">Chapter 4</span>
                    <h3 class="chap-title">Lights, Camera... Panic!</h3>
                </div>
                <p class="chap-teaser">Ravi experiences the terrifying pressures of celebrity PR shoots, while Aryan discovers what it truly feels like to be completely broke and invisible.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="chapter-card">
                <div>
                    <span class="chap-num">Chapter 5</span>
                    <h3 class="chap-title">Echoes of the Forgotten</h3>
                </div>
                <p class="chap-teaser">Aryan discovers a scrapbook of sacrifices that changes his entire worldview, prompting him to find local radio work to rebuild Ravi's life.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="chapter-card">
                <div>
                    <span class="chap-num">Chapter 6</span>
                    <h3 class="chap-title">The Revival Begins</h3>
                </div>
                <p class="chap-teaser">Ravi strips Aryan's identity of arrogance, stunning movie sets with pure vulnerability, while Aryan captures real hearts using only his raw voice over local airwaves.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="chapter-card">
                <div>
                    <span class="chap-num">Chapter 7</span>
                    <h3 class="chap-title">Two Lives Rewritten</h3>
                </div>
                <p class="chap-teaser">The swap fosters a profound internal healing. Real connections bloom in Rajahmundry, and critical film teasers hint at a historic cinematic resurrection.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="chapter-card">
                <div>
                    <span class="chap-num">Chapter 8</span>
                    <h3 class="chap-title">The Day the World Noticed</h3>
                </div>
                <p class="chap-teaser">An emotional performance earns critical standing ovations. However, an astute blind fan's viral recording threatens to trigger complete exposure.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="chapter-card">
                <div>
                    <span class="chap-num">Chapter 9</span>
                    <h3 class="chap-title">The Reckoning</h3>
                </div>
                <p class="chap-teaser">As suspicion reaches a breaking point, a high-stakes press conference forces Ravi to make a choice between running or delivering profound raw truth.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="chapter-card">
                <div>
                    <span class="chap-num">Chapter 10</span>
                    <h3 class="chap-title">The Price of Becoming</h3>
                </div>
                <p class="chap-teaser">Dark past secrets leak to the press. A dangerous kidnapping trap organized by an old manager forces the two men to unite in physical combat.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="chapter-card">
                <div>
                    <span class="chap-num">Chapter 11</span>
                    <h3 class="chap-title">Full Circle</h3>
                </div>
                <p class="chap-teaser">The cosmic circle completes under the Mumbai rain. Reclaiming their original skins, they return not as idol and fan, but as transformed equals.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- QUOTES SECTION -->
    <section id="quotes" style="background-color: #090c12;">
        <span class="section-label">Dialogue & Musings</span>
        <h2 class="section-title">Echoes of <span>Truth</span></h2>
        
        <div class="featured-quote-container">
            <p class="featured-quote-text">"To the world, he's a fading star. To me, he's the only light that never gave up on me."</p>
            <span class="featured-quote-author">— Ravi's Letter, Chapter 5</span>
        </div>

        <div class="quotes-grid">
            <div class="quote-card">
                <p class="quote-text">"While we struggle for groceries, you print banners for a fallen star!"</p>
                <span class="quote-context">— Ravi's Mother, Chapter 1[cite: 1]</span>
            </div>
            <div class="quote-card">
                <p class="quote-text">"Maybe someone else should carry this burden... anyone but me."</p>
                <span class="quote-context">— Aryan Kapoor, Chapter 2</span>
            </div>
            <div class="quote-card">
                <p class="quote-text">"He's... human now... The arrogance was gone. The tantrums too."</p>
                <span class="quote-context">— Production Crew, Chapter 6</span>
            </div>
            <div class="quote-card">
                <p class="quote-text">"You were a warrior. You saved me when I didn't even deserve saving."</p>
                <span class="quote-context">— Aryan's Reflection, Chapter 6</span>
            </div>
            <div class="quote-card">
                <p class="quote-text">"You don't measure talent by popularity."</p>
                <span class="quote-context">— Ravi as Aryan, Chapter 7</span>
            </div>
            <div class="quote-card">
                <p class="quote-text">"When you have even one person who believes in your redemption, you change."</p>
                <span class="quote-context">— Aryan as Ravi, Chapter 10</span>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- JOURNEY / TIMELINE SECTION -->
    <section id="journey">
        <span class="section-label">The Metamorphosis</span>
        <h2 class="section-title">The Path of <span>Redemption</span></h2>
        
        <div class="timeline">
            <div class="timeline-item">
                <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
                <span class="timeline-stage">Beginning</span>
                <h3 class="timeline-title">Isolated Realities</h3>
                <p class="timeline-desc">Ravi celebrates Aryan's birthday alone in a crumbling hall in Rajahmundry[cite: 1], while in Mumbai, Aryan wallows in alcohol and toxic media loops.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="timeline-item">
                <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
                <span class="timeline-stage">Early Conflict</span>
                <h3 class="timeline-title">The Celestial Incident</h3>
                <p class="timeline-desc">Simultaneous, desperate cosmic wishes spark thunder over an unclouded sky[cite: 1], causing their physical identities and bodies to fully swap.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="timeline-item">
                <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
                <span class="timeline-stage">Relationship Growth</span>
                <h3 class="timeline-title">Unseen Acts of Service</h3>
                <p class="timeline-desc">Aryan reads Ravi's personal scrapbook of sacrifices and begins restructuring Ravi's family life. Meanwhile, Ravi strips Aryan's career of toxic arrogance.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="timeline-item">
                <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
                <span class="timeline-stage">Major Turning Point</span>
                <h3 class="timeline-title">The Rise of Veracity</h3>
                <p class="timeline-desc">Ravi delivers a monumental, emotionally honest acting performance in an indie film, while Aryan finds joy as a voice actor over local radio slots.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="timeline-item">
                <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
                <span class="timeline-stage">Crisis</span>
                <h3 class="timeline-title">The Leaks & The Trap</h3>
                <p class="timeline-desc">Old industry controversies unravel publicly. Corrupt ex-manager Vikas Rawat smells the identity shift and kidnaps Ravi for multi-million blackmail.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="timeline-item">
                <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
                <span class="timeline-stage">Climax</span>
                <h3 class="timeline-title">Warehouse Reckoning</h3>
                <p class="timeline-desc">Aryan races to Mumbai, tracking down the warehouse. Standing side by side, they fight off the criminals and present a unified, honest front to the media.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="timeline-item">
                <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
                <span class="timeline-stage">Resolution</span>
                <h3 class="timeline-title">The Exhale of the Void</h3>
                <p class="timeline-desc">The golden thread returns them to their true physical forms. They return to their distinct cities, no longer divided as idol and fan, but bound as equals.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ENDING SECTION -->
    <section id="ending" style="background-color: #070a0f;">
        <div class="ending-container">
            <span class="section-label">The Final Curtain</span>
            <blockquote class="ending-quote">
                "Not who you were... but who you choose to be."
            </blockquote>
            <div class="ending-reflection">
                <p>The journey of <em>Fan to Fame</em> culminates not in the retention of magical grandeur, but in the ultimate realization of self-worth. By stepping into each other’s storms, both men successfully healed the voids inside themselves. Aryan discovered the grounding power of humility and true connection, while Ravi found a unique voice and personal identity that existed independently of his posters.</p>
                <p>As the cosmic thread faded, it left behind two distinct men who could look directly into their respective mirrors and finally, truly, smile at the reflection looking back.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- FOOTER SECTION -->
    <footer>
        <h3 class="footer-title">FAN TO FAME</h3>
        <p class="footer-author">Deva Harsha V</p>
        <p class="footer-quote">"Sometimes, when alone in the silence of a starlit night, each one would remember what it felt like to look into a mirror... and smile."</p>
    </footer>

    <!-- INTERACTIVE NAV SCRIPT -->
    <script>
        document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
            const sections = document.querySelectorAll('section');
            const navLinks = document.querySelectorAll('.nav-links a');

            window.addEventListener('scroll', () => {
                let current = '';
                sections.forEach(section => {
                    const sectionTop = section.offsetTop;
                    const sectionHeight = section.clientHeight;
                    if (pageYOffset >= (sectionTop - 200)) {
                        current = section.getAttribute('id');
                    }
                });

                navLinks.forEach(link => {
                    link.classList.remove('active');
                    if (link.getAttribute('href').slice(1) === current) {
                        link.classList.add('active');
                    }
                });
            });
        });
    </script>
    <%- include('partials/footer') %>